<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet follow me</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> puts the pet in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Follow</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mode.  This is the initial mode of a newly summoned pet.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet guard here</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> puts the pet in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Guard</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mode.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet sit down</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> puts the pet in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sit</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mode.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet attack</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> puts the owners current target at the top <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (?)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of the pet's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and ends <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hold</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Unless <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Player versus Player</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is enabled, you cannot add a player or a player charmed NPC to a pet's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet kill name</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> takes whatever would be selected by the command <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /target name</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (?) and puts it at the top <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (?)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of the pet's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  While it is not entirely clear what the most distant range this command will add to the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the target may be outside <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Attack Range</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and thus not immediately attacked.  This command also ends <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hold</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet back off</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> empties the pet's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, causing it to stop attacking.  However, there are no guarantees that the pet's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> will stay empty for long, so it may immediately resume attacking.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet hold</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> causes the pet to be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Held</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, that is, it ignores its <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and goes into <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Free</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mode, resuming its regular movement <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (either follow, guard, or sit)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  The pet does however continue to maintain its <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which it will act upon as soon as either <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet attack</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet kill<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  are issued.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is only available to level 59 or higher <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> who have obtained the magician class AA skill <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Pet Discipline</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet taunt off</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> disables pet taunting, that is the pet will not taunt during fights.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet taunt on</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> enables pet taunting.<br>
